[% META
        title = "Carton Dependency Management for Catalyst Applications"
   description = "Guide to standardizing Perl dependency management using Carton for consistent, reproducible environments"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "developer"
   page_version = "1.00"
   last_updated = "Fri Oct 17 09:00:46 AM PDT 2025"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/developer/carton_dependency_management.tt,v 1.00 09:00:46 2025/10/17 shanta Exp shanta - Carton Dependency Management Documentation' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Carton Dependency Management for Catalyst Applications</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-10-17 | 
        Version: 1.0 | 
        Author: Shanta | 
        Status: Active
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">This guide explains how to standardize Perl dependency management using Carton to ensure reproducible dependencies across development, staging, and production environments, eliminating version mismatches and system Perl conflicts.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Catalyst application already installed</li>
                <li>Admin access to development and production VMs</li>
                <li>Git repository access for committing dependency files</li>
                <li>R710 Catalyst VM and workstation dev VM access</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Key Benefits</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Version Consistency</strong>: Identical dependencies across all environments</li>
                <li><strong>Isolation</strong>: Local dependency installation prevents system conflicts</li>
                <li><strong>Reproducibility</strong>: Exact dependency versions tracked in version control</li>
                <li><strong>Safety</strong>: No system Perl modifications required</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Getting Started</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 1: Install Carton</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Install Carton globally on your system using cpanm.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Install Carton globally
cpanm Carton
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 2: Create cpanfile</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Create a cpanfile in your Catalyst application's root directory to define all dependencies.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Create cpanfile in your Catalyst app's root directory
# /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv/cpanfile

requires 'Catalyst::Runtime', '5.90129';
requires 'Catalyst::Devel';
requires 'Starman', '0.4015';
requires 'DBIx::Class';
requires 'Template';
requires 'Moose';
requires 'Email::Sender::Simple';
requires 'JSON';
requires 'YAML::XS';
requires 'DateTime';
requires 'Log::Log4perl';

# Development dependencies (optional)
on 'develop' => sub {
    requires 'Test::More';
    requires 'Test::Pod';
    requires 'Test::Pod::Coverage';
    requires 'Test::WWW::Mechanize::Catalyst';
};
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Step 3: Install Dependencies</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Install all dependencies into a local directory using Carton.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Navigate to your Catalyst application directory
cd /home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv

# Install dependencies locally
carton install
                </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Advanced Usage</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Running Your Application with Carton</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Always use carton exec to run your application with the proper dependency isolation.</p>

            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Run with Starman server
carton exec plackup -s Starman -p 5000 app.psgi

# Run development server
carton exec script/comserv_server.pl

# Run any Perl script with isolated dependencies
carton exec perl your_script.pl
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Version Control Integration</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Commit dependency files to ensure consistent environments across all deployments.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Add dependency files to Git
git add cpanfile cpanfile.snapshot
git commit -m "Add Carton dependency management"
git push origin main

# Note: Do NOT commit the local/ directory - add it to .gitignore
echo "local/" >> .gitignore
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Production Deployment</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Deploy with exact dependency versions on production servers.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# On production server after code deployment
cd /path/to/catalyst/app
carton install --deployment

# This ensures exact versions from cpanfile.snapshot are used
# and no development dependencies are installed
                </code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: Module Not Found After carton install</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Application fails to start with "Can't locate Module/Name.pm in @INC"</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Always use <code>carton exec</code> prefix when running your application or any Perl commands</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: Version Conflicts Between Environments</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Code works in development but fails in production due to different module versions</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Ensure cpanfile.snapshot is committed and use <code>carton install --deployment</code> in production</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">Problem: Carton Command Not Found</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> "carton: command not found" error</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Install Carton globally with <code>cpanm Carton</code> or ensure your Perl bin directory is in your PATH</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Command Reference</h2>
            
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <tr>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Command</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Purpose</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Environment</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">carton install</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Install all dependencies locally</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Development</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">carton install --deployment</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Install exact versions from snapshot</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Production</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">carton exec [command]</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Run command with local dependencies</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">All</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">carton list</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Show installed dependencies</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">All</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">carton update [module]</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Update specific module or all modules</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Development</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="success" style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Migration Checklist</h2>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li>✓ Install Carton globally on all servers</li>
                    <li>✓ Create cpanfile with all current dependencies</li>
                    <li>✓ Run <code>carton install</code> to generate local/ and cpanfile.snapshot</li>
                    <li>✓ Update startup scripts to use <code>carton exec</code></li>
                    <li>✓ Add cpanfile and cpanfile.snapshot to version control</li>
                    <li>✓ Add local/ to .gitignore</li>
                    <li>✓ Deploy and test in staging environment</li>
                    <li>✓ Deploy to production using <code>--deployment</code> flag</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div class="success" style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">See Also</h2>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/developer/catalyst_deployment" style="color: var(--link-color);">Catalyst Deployment Guide</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/system/database_configuration" style="color: var(--link-color);">Database Configuration</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/admin/server_update_procedure" style="color: var(--link-color);">Server Update Procedure</a></li>
                    <li><a href="https://metacpan.org/pod/Carton" style="color: var(--link-color);">Official Carton Documentation</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large); padding-top: var(--spacing-medium); border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <p>For technical support or questions about dependency management, contact the system administrator.</p>
                <p><em>This documentation is part of the Comserv system development guidelines.</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- 
IMPLEMENTATION NOTES:

This documentation covers the complete Carton workflow for Catalyst applications:

1. **Dependency Management Benefits**:
   - Eliminates version conflicts between dev/staging/prod
   - Provides local dependency installation (no system Perl changes)
   - Ensures reproducible builds across environments

2. **Key Files**:
   - cpanfile: Dependency declarations (human-readable)
   - cpanfile.snapshot: Exact versions (auto-generated)
   - local/: Installation directory (auto-created, not versioned)

3. **Workflow**:
   - Development: carton install (installs latest compatible versions)
   - Production: carton install --deployment (uses exact snapshot versions)
   - Execution: Always use carton exec prefix

4. **Hardware Compatibility**:
   - Works on existing R710 Catalyst VM
   - Compatible with workstation dev VM
   - No system modifications required

This approach eliminates the manual CPAN update risks mentioned in the original request.
-->